Vehicle inheritance example.
This example explains the inheritance in the part where our classes go and car extends its components of the vehicle class,
which is the base class of this example and shares its methods with the other classes.

Whenever we want to resolve the inheritance paradigm, we must take into account the answer to the question is it a?
My truck is a vehicle and my car is a vehicle, this means that the parent class will be a vehicle.

Employees inheritance example.
In this example, our parent class is the class employees since answering again the question is it a?
We can realize that a boss will always be an employee, who will have some more particular characteristics but
will always share those of an employee


